snippet.textDisplay: @The Game Changer  I got auto-immune hepatitis, not Hep B or any other known viral type of hepatitis.  Hep B (unlike C) is contagious by saliva.  Nurses taking care of Hep B patients often developed immunity with out getting sick much, if at all, as saliva delivers a much lower viral load.  The problem is with children because they don't have the immune system yet, and they become chronic for life if they get it too young.  I have also heard, you can get a really bad immune reaction from the vaccine if you already had viral Hep B before they stick you.

snippet.textDisplay: @Liam Lab animals that were eating GMO food almost exclusively showed a whole lot of trouble, i.e., organ failure.  Humans don't usually eat Soy, Corn, Canola, that exclusively, so it is less severe.   The studies HAVE been buried.  But, people with pets have seen the trouble in their pets as kibble has contained a lot of soy and corn and love of those pets has created a strong market for soy and corn free pet food.  It hard to ignore the difference GMO vs non-GMO food makes in your pet.  Also, the documentary King Corn shows the trouble corn-fed beef experience, although they don't mention the GMO aspect that much.
